criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Is at least 17 years of age and has full legal capacity to volunteer;

          -  Has read and signed an information consent letter;

          -  Is willing and able to follow instructions and maintain the appointment schedule;

          -  Is an adapted soft contact lens wearer;

          -  Has a contact lens prescription between +4.00 to -6.00D;

          -  Has astigmatism <= 1.00D;

          -  Has vision of 20/40 or better in both eyes when wearing contact lenses

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Is participating in any concurrent clinical or research study;

          -  Has any known active ocular disease and/or infection;

          -  Has a systemic condition that in the opinion of the investigator may affect a study
             outcome variable;

          -  Is using any systemic or topical medications that in the opinion of the investigator
             may affect a study outcome variable;

          -  Has known sensitivity to the diagnostic pharmaceuticals to be used in the study;

          -  Is pregnant, lactating or planning a pregnancy at the time of enrolment, determined
             verbally;

          -  Is aphakic;

          -  Has undergone refractive surgery;

          -  Is an employee of the Centre for Contact Lens Research;

          -  Has anisometropia of >=1.00D

          -  Has a difference in comfort of 20 (on a 0-100 scale) between eyes when not wearing
             contact lenses.
